exercises.solutionExplanation:
■ Switch expression (arrow syntax →): A new switch syntax available since Java 14. No break needed, no fall-through.
■ yield keyword: Used to return a value from a block within a switch expression.
■ Switch expression assignment: Can be directly assigned to a variable: String result = switch(x) { ... };

